WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.130 --> 00:00:25.070
Good news. everyone!

2
00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.480
Well? What is it?

3
00:00:29.470 --> 00:00:30.800
What is what?

4
00:00:30.810 --> 00:00:32.210
Oh! Right!

5
00:00:32.210 --> 00:00:38.020
Ladies and gentlemen. we'll be delivering
this mysterious crate to Peebles Alpha.

6
00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:41.710
Peebles Alpha? The planet
of gangs. thugs and hustlers?

7
00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:43.480
Ooh! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

8
00:00:43.490 --> 00:00:47.490
Hang on. If we're delivering a package
to criminals. I want to know what's in it.

9
00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:49.890
I have no idea. Leela.

10
00:00:49.890 --> 00:00:52.750
But I'll tell you the
same thing they told me...

11
00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:56.240
Stop asking questions. old man. and
we'll slip you an extra five grand

12
00:00:56.230 --> 00:01:00.910
that your crew doesn't
need to know about.

13
00:01:01.510 --> 00:01:03.680
Now. listen carefully.

14
00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:06.810
This planet is controlled
by two rival gangs...

15
00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:08.570
the Blips and the Cruds.

16
00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:12.720
You can tell them apart by
their colors... red and blue.

17
00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:14.760
Which gang's red. and which gang's blue?

18
00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:16.350
Both!

19
00:01:16.350 --> 00:01:19.750
The delivery is going to the
Blips. so when you meet them.

20
00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:22.500
you'll want to be wearing these jerseys.

21
00:01:22.490 --> 00:01:24.560
Not these jerseys.

22
00:01:24.560 --> 00:01:27.660
Because if you're wearing these.
you'll be killed on the spot.

23
00:01:27.670 --> 00:01:30.240
Okay. here are your jerseys.

24
00:01:30.230 --> 00:01:32.870
No. wait. Here.

25
00:01:33.240 --> 00:01:35.580
No. Wait...

26
00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:45.210
Does anyone else find
this delivery suspicious?

27
00:01:45.220 --> 00:01:48.220
Nope. He's too dumb. and I don't care.

28
00:01:48.220 --> 00:01:50.290
Well. I'm smart. and I care too much.

29
00:01:50.290 --> 00:01:52.430
I want to know what's in that crate.

30
00:01:52.420 --> 00:01:53.920
But we're not allowed to open it!

31
00:01:53.920 --> 00:01:56.690
I know that! Go get me a crowbar.

32
00:01:56.690 --> 00:01:58.460
Please. use mine.

33
00:01:58.460 --> 00:02:02.930
I just need it in case. uh. Fry gets
his head stuck in a pot of honey.

34
00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:05.430
And in the meantime. if I should happen

35
00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:10.090
to bump into the crate
and open it... whoopsie!

36
00:02:10.090 --> 00:02:13.330
Hey. Leela. Fry got his
head stuck in a pot of honey!

37
00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:15.110
Oh. bother.

38
00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:17.270
Not now!

39
00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:26.420
What is it? Alcohol? Tobacco? Firearms?

40
00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:27.640
Firearms!

41
00:02:27.640 --> 00:02:32.260
That's the one I was
secretly hoping for.

42
00:02:33.460 --> 00:02:36.850
I'm okay with most kinds of
violence. but not gang violence.

43
00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:38.660
Before we deliver these weapons.

44
00:02:38.670 --> 00:02:41.710
we're going to disable them
so they can never be used.

45
00:02:41.710 --> 00:02:43.710
Bender. bend the barrels.

46
00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:45.340
But I love guns!

47
00:02:45.340 --> 00:02:47.240
Then pretend they're little human necks.

48
00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:50.360
What?! Let me at 'em!

49
00:03:02.270 --> 00:03:07.310
A lot of ships get stolen on this planet.
so. Bender. stay here and stand guard.

50
00:03:07.310 --> 00:03:11.450
Okay. I hope I never see you again.

51
00:03:19.410 --> 00:03:22.320
Uh. I don't like the looks of
this gang-infested neighborhood.

52
00:03:22.330 --> 00:03:23.790
There might be spiders!

53
00:03:23.790 --> 00:03:25.460
We must have made a wrong turn.

54
00:03:25.450 --> 00:03:27.450
We should have reached Blip turf by now.

55
00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:29.690
You think we walked
straight out of Blipton?

56
00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:32.970
Wait. there's some Blips.

57
00:03:32.960 --> 00:03:34.760
Those aren't Blips! They're Cruds!

58
00:03:34.760 --> 00:03:36.290
They have the red on the left.

59
00:03:36.300 --> 00:03:39.780
Oh. no! What should we do?

60
00:03:39.900 --> 00:03:42.770
Leela. this is no time
to show me your boobs!

61
00:03:42.770 --> 00:03:45.130
Turn your jersey inside out.

62
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:48.020
Oh. Show me again.

63
00:03:51.550 --> 00:03:53.990
Yo. what you doing on our turf?

64
00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:55.480
Chill. dawg. Ain't no thang.

65
00:03:55.480 --> 00:03:57.050
We Cruds.

66
00:03:57.050 --> 00:04:01.010
Well. we Blips. and we over here.

67
00:04:01.590 --> 00:04:04.550
We put up that mirror because
this is a blind intersection.

68
00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:07.550
It's considerably reduced
the number of accidents.

69
00:04:07.540 --> 00:04:10.000
It don't do nothing for
the murder rate. though.

70
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:15.060
Now get down on your knees so
we can blow your Crud brains out!

71
00:04:15.070 --> 00:04:17.510
Um. Leela. remember when
we were trying to guess

72
00:04:17.510 --> 00:04:19.640
what would happen if someone
stuck a gun in my face.

73
00:04:19.640 --> 00:04:21.970
and you said I'd probably crap my pants?

74
00:04:21.980 --> 00:04:23.650
- Well...
- Excuse me. Sir?

75
00:04:23.650 --> 00:04:26.140
We're not actually Blips or Cruds.

76
00:04:26.140 --> 00:04:28.790
We're delivery people.
here to deliver this crate.

77
00:04:28.780 --> 00:04:32.780
So if everything seems to be in
order. we'll be on our way. a'ight?

78
00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:34.760
Oh. it's far from a'ight.

79
00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:36.430
Now. hold up!

80
00:04:36.420 --> 00:04:38.290
It's a'ight. all right?

81
00:04:38.290 --> 00:04:42.370
It's a Crud. and he's got a gun!

82
00:04:42.990 --> 00:04:45.900
Yo. you just shot your own
reflection in the mirror.

83
00:04:45.900 --> 00:04:47.410
It was self-defense.

84
00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:49.770
We are the Cruds. but we're over here.

85
00:04:49.770 --> 00:04:52.700
And don't shoot. That
crate is a gift from us.

86
00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:53.550
- What?!
- Huh?

87
00:04:53.540 --> 00:04:54.640
For real?

88
00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:56.870
There's been enough
violence on these streets.

89
00:04:56.870 --> 00:04:59.370
Too many lives and mirrors
have been shattered.

90
00:04:59.380 --> 00:05:02.990
So. yo. we sent you a crate
of weapons as a sign of trust.

91
00:05:02.980 --> 00:05:07.050
Together. we can use them to rid
our streets of the real enemy.

92
00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:09.530
- Giant spiders.
- I knew it!

93
00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:11.420
Man. that's a nice gesture.

94
00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:13.800
We accept your offer of peace.

95
00:05:13.800 --> 00:05:17.370
Let's just have a look at
these top-quality weapons.

96
00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:19.910
I'll test it out on
that innocent bystander.

97
00:05:19.900 --> 00:05:21.370
Ow!

98
00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:23.690
Yo. you just shot yourself again!

99
00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:26.920
It's a trick! Get 'em!

100
00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:29.280
Ow. Oh.

101
00:05:39.320 --> 00:05:42.130
Look. let's just agree
that gang violence

102
00:05:42.130 --> 00:05:44.720
is an important issue
with no easy answers.

103
00:05:44.730 --> 00:05:45.660
Okay.

104
00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:47.690
Anyway. the ship's still here.

105
00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:51.500
- And nothing was stolen.
- Yeah it was!

106
00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:54.240
I got bot-jacked!

107
00:05:54.240 --> 00:05:57.010
All I have left is my cigar.

108
00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.040
Wait...

109
00:06:04.870 --> 00:06:07.540
They stole everything
except my mouth and eyes.

110
00:06:07.530 --> 00:06:10.400
I guess they didn't like
all my screaming and winking.

111
00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:13.230
It's just lucky Bender
had a RoJack installed.

112
00:06:13.240 --> 00:06:18.900
When I activate it. the police
should be able to locate him.

113
00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:21.600
Locating... locating...

114
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:23.690
Located.

115
00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:29.680
It's a robot chop shop.

116
00:06:29.690 --> 00:06:32.840
That's some primordial evil.

117
00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:35.870
This Skell here buys stolen
robots. strips 'em down.

118
00:06:35.860 --> 00:06:37.860
and sells the parts all over the galaxy.

119
00:06:37.870 --> 00:06:42.970
Okay. I'm getting a signal
from Bender's RoJack.

120
00:06:43.270 --> 00:06:45.540
Naw. it's just a piece of junk.

121
00:06:45.540 --> 00:06:48.250
That's not junk! That's Bender's head!

122
00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:51.020
My head?! Slap me upside it!

123
00:06:51.030 --> 00:06:53.120
Ah. home. sweet head.

124
00:06:53.110 --> 00:06:55.140
That's it? Where's the rest of him?

125
00:06:55.150 --> 00:06:56.720
All other parts sold.

126
00:06:56.720 --> 00:06:58.560
But I have list of buyers.

127
00:06:58.550 --> 00:07:00.940
You drop charges. I give you list.

128
00:07:00.940 --> 00:07:03.940
No dice. Justice don't work that way.

129
00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:05.100
Wait. Wait.

130
00:07:05.100 --> 00:07:09.050
What if I throw in giant
robot head for nice officer?

131
00:07:09.050 --> 00:07:11.030
Hmm...

132
00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:13.000
Thanks for all your help. officer!

133
00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.400
My pleasure.

134
00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:18.870
Boy. Bender. you sure
were chock full of parts.

135
00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.010
I didn't even know you had a wishbone.

136
00:07:21.020 --> 00:07:23.080
I had a lot of magic things.

137
00:07:23.080 --> 00:07:24.950
And we'll never get them all back.

138
00:07:24.950 --> 00:07:26.620
Oh. sure we will.

139
00:07:26.610 --> 00:07:28.670
If we live a really long time.

140
00:07:28.670 --> 00:07:31.550
Let's get started.

141
00:07:44.460 --> 00:07:46.100
Come in. come in.

142
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:48.580
Close the door. You're
letting the smut out.

143
00:07:48.580 --> 00:07:50.240
All right. buddy.

144
00:07:50.230 --> 00:07:52.730
We know for a fact that
you received a stolen item.

145
00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:56.060
A certain sensitive part of my Anatomy.

146
00:07:56.060 --> 00:07:57.650
What. you mean your antenna?

147
00:07:57.640 --> 00:07:59.600
Shh! Watch your language.

148
00:07:59.610 --> 00:08:01.480
This ain't a church. lady.

149
00:08:01.490 --> 00:08:03.380
Except for tax purposes.

150
00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:04.720
Anyway. I can't help you.

151
00:08:04.730 --> 00:08:07.430
One of my customers already
bought your friend's antenna.

152
00:08:07.430 --> 00:08:09.960
Oh. excuse me... Robo-Dong.

153
00:08:09.950 --> 00:08:11.620
Who was it? Can you give us a name?

154
00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:12.820
Certainly not.

155
00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:15.890
I could never betray
a customer's privacy.

156
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:21.790
All I can give you is this naked
picture of him taken from my toilet cam.

157
00:08:23.900 --> 00:08:25.750
I'll get right to the point. Senator.

158
00:08:25.760 --> 00:08:28.520
You purchased our friend's...

159
00:08:28.530 --> 00:08:29.930
Antenna.

160
00:08:29.930 --> 00:08:31.180
We'd like it back.

161
00:08:31.180 --> 00:08:33.960
You may have it. I'm through with it.

162
00:08:33.970 --> 00:08:37.180
It has done everything
and everyone imaginable.

163
00:08:37.170 --> 00:08:39.610
You may want to get it disinfected.

164
00:08:39.620 --> 00:08:41.720
Can do.

165
00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:57.690
Sorry. guys. I'm gonna
have to confiscate your keg.

166
00:08:57.690 --> 00:08:59.020
It's my body.

167
00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:02.050
Oh. come on. Bender! Can you
at least wait till it's empty?

168
00:09:02.050 --> 00:09:05.470
Fair enough. Fry. beer me.

169
00:09:11.330 --> 00:09:13.730
It's empty!

170
00:09:15.190 --> 00:09:18.190
I'm 40% back. baby!

171
00:09:26.010 --> 00:09:29.150
Sorry. but these robot arms have
brought me nothing but luck...

172
00:09:29.160 --> 00:09:31.920
With the cards...

173
00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:35.420
And with the ladies.

174
00:09:35.420 --> 00:09:36.140
Sir!

175
00:09:36.140 --> 00:09:37.690
But those are my arms!

176
00:09:37.690 --> 00:09:39.860
That's Gropey. and that's Cheaty.

177
00:09:39.860 --> 00:09:41.960
Cheaty?!

178
00:09:44.210 --> 00:09:45.910
Now. gentlemen. I'm sure we can...

179
00:09:45.910 --> 00:09:47.710
Oh!

180
00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:51.340
Well. then. I'll just collect
my winnings and be on my...

181
00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:53.140
Oh!

182
00:09:55.770 --> 00:09:58.230
Much obliged.

183
00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:05.300
All right. Tinny. your double
leg transplant is complete.

184
00:10:05.300 --> 00:10:09.500
What do you say you give 'em a try?

185
00:10:13.330 --> 00:10:16.930
It's a miracle! I can walk!

186
00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:19.480
No more crutch or withered leg!

187
00:10:19.490 --> 00:10:22.510
Someone's sure to adopt me now!

188
00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:25.710
Well. Bender. I guess you
won't be getting your legs back.

189
00:10:25.710 --> 00:10:31.610
But your sacrifice will let an innocent
child live a full and happy life.

190
00:10:33.050 --> 00:10:34.780
I'm sorry. You were saying something?

191
00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:36.210
Oh. crumb.

192
00:10:36.220 --> 00:10:40.600
I guess it's back to the cart for me.

193
00:10:41.790 --> 00:10:44.430
Ooh. nice cart.

194
00:10:47.370 --> 00:10:49.450
Hey. this thing's pretty smooth.

195
00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:52.810
Eh. but I still prefer walking.

196
00:10:52.800 --> 00:10:55.870
Well. we did it... we got
all Bender's parts back.

197
00:10:55.870 --> 00:10:57.480
Wrong as always. Fry!

198
00:10:57.490 --> 00:11:00.540
I'm still missing the
shiniest metal piece of all.

199
00:11:00.540 --> 00:11:01.670
Your thyroid?

200
00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:04.470
No! I'm talking about my ass!

201
00:11:04.460 --> 00:11:08.840
Huh. I never even knew you had an ass.

202
00:11:10.020 --> 00:11:15.920
Hmm. According to this. it shipped out on
a freighter from South Street Spaceport.

203
00:11:18.340 --> 00:11:20.720
Oh. yes. I remember that ass.

204
00:11:20.730 --> 00:11:22.360
Let's see...

205
00:11:22.370 --> 00:11:24.220
Oh. God. no!

206
00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:27.030
<i>It was on board the Floatwell!</i>

207
00:11:27.030 --> 00:11:29.910
The ship that sank in
that horrible space storm?

208
00:11:29.910 --> 00:11:33.250
Yes. I'm afraid your friend's
derriere is lost forever

209
00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:36.000
in the depths of the Sargaseous Sea.

210
00:11:36.010 --> 00:11:37.230
My ass!

211
00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:39.350
Sweet love of my life!

212
00:11:39.350 --> 00:11:42.890
Several hundred people
died. too. including my wife.

213
00:11:42.890 --> 00:11:44.990
My ass!

214
00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:46.600
I'm sorry. buddy.

215
00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:48.120
Maybe we can get you a new one.

216
00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:49.390
Never!

217
00:11:49.390 --> 00:11:51.560
My ass is my soul mate.

218
00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:53.620
It even has its own hind-brain.

219
00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:56.070
Really? Your butt can think?

220
00:11:56.070 --> 00:11:58.160
No. But it can feel.

221
00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:00.990
And right now. it's hind-heartbroken!

222
00:12:00.990 --> 00:12:03.510
Just like me!

223
00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:08.450
Wow. Bender. this is really
important to you. isn't it?

224
00:12:08.450 --> 00:12:10.270
Uh-huh.

225
00:12:10.270 --> 00:12:16.170
Okay. we're gonna find that shipwreck
and get you your backside back.

226
00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:19.620
Okay. let's go.

227
00:12:32.300 --> 00:12:35.330
The ship carrying Bender's heinie
sank in the treacherous gases

228
00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:36.940
of the Sargaseous Sea.

229
00:12:36.940 --> 00:12:38.940
Once we locate the wreck...

230
00:12:38.940 --> 00:12:41.160
<i>Asteroids!</i>

231
00:12:46.350 --> 00:12:48.350
<i>Curse this interstellar fog.</i>

232
00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:51.210
Why isn't there a lighthouse
to guide us away from the rocks?

233
00:12:51.220 --> 00:12:56.260
I don't know. but look
out for that lighthouse!

234
00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:07.970
So you're alive. are ye?

235
00:13:07.970 --> 00:13:10.830
I suppose you'll be wanting
to keep your tooth fillin's.

236
00:13:10.840 --> 00:13:11.960
Are ye hurt?

237
00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:15.390
No. but we could use a hug.

238
00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:18.620
Better come inside then.

239
00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:21.990
Name's Tarquin.

240
00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:26.530
Been alone here. tending this
light. longer'n I can remember.

241
00:13:26.530 --> 00:13:28.160
That'll be my Cup-a-Soup.

242
00:13:28.150 --> 00:13:31.230
It's been microwavin'
longer'n I can remember.

243
00:13:31.230 --> 00:13:32.830
This is a dangerous coast.

244
00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:35.300
We didn't see your light
until it was too late.

245
00:13:35.300 --> 00:13:38.130
No beam can pierce that devilish mist.

246
00:13:38.140 --> 00:13:42.310
Shipwrecks be so common. I make a good
living out of whatever washes ashore.

247
00:13:42.310 --> 00:13:44.850
Found me a whole Blue Man Group once.

248
00:13:44.850 --> 00:13:46.580
So you have two jobs?

249
00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:52.010
More. I also salvage the wrecks with
my bathysphere. and I'm a butcher.

250
00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:54.590
if you like blue meat.

251
00:13:54.590 --> 00:13:57.100
Sounds good. but about
that bathysphere...

252
00:13:57.090 --> 00:14:00.990
We want to salvage a cargo ship that
sank carrying this robot's rear end.

253
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:04.640
Aye. I'll help ye for
a cut of the booty.

254
00:14:04.630 --> 00:14:07.430
Now. when you say a cut of the booty...

255
00:14:07.430 --> 00:14:10.200
I mean a percentage of the
value of the recovered goods.

256
00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:11.700
Now be getting some rest.

257
00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:15.430
The booty call is at daybreak.

258
00:15:09.360 --> 00:15:11.890
Those sound like
one-eyed corpse screams.

259
00:15:11.900 --> 00:15:16.160
Oh. I wish I was down there with ye.

260
00:15:17.510 --> 00:15:19.270
Let's not forget that this shipwreck

261
00:15:19.270 --> 00:15:23.170
is also the final resting
place of this brave Captain.

262
00:15:23.180 --> 00:15:24.620
Place your bets.

263
00:15:24.610 --> 00:15:26.530
Whee!

264
00:15:34.170 --> 00:15:36.510
That's it. I'm sure!

265
00:15:36.520 --> 00:15:40.340
I can tell by the words on the crate!

266
00:15:40.330 --> 00:15:42.200
Oh. my beloved.

267
00:15:42.210 --> 00:15:44.910
You complete me.

268
00:15:52.820 --> 00:15:54.370
Hurry on inside now.

269
00:15:54.380 --> 00:15:55.570
Storm's a-brewin'.

270
00:15:55.570 --> 00:16:00.070
I can feel it in my weather channel app.

271
00:16:01.300 --> 00:16:03.120
<i>Soon the sea will be belchin'</i>

272
00:16:03.130 --> 00:16:04.970
<i>her dead upon the shore.</i>

273
00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:10.860
If ye like your shoes unmatched and with
feet still in 'em. this is your night.

274
00:16:14.290 --> 00:16:16.440
Can't you make the beacon any brighter?

275
00:16:16.440 --> 00:16:19.800
Nay. 'tis already the brightest
object in the known Universe.

276
00:16:19.810 --> 00:16:21.630
<i>and even so. it can't be seen</i>

277
00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:25.880
<i>three feet away in a storm like this.</i>

278
00:16:30.490 --> 00:16:33.550
I thought we were near the rocks.
but I don't see the lighthouse.

279
00:16:33.550 --> 00:16:36.660
so everything is fine and we can relax.

280
00:16:36.660 --> 00:16:40.370
All hands on deck for Mojitos.

281
00:16:40.360 --> 00:16:43.660
The important thing is I
got my final piece back.

282
00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:47.380
Hey. Fry. take a picture of me
biting my own shiny metal ass.

283
00:16:47.370 --> 00:16:50.070
I'd be honored.

284
00:16:58.900 --> 00:16:59.900
Ah.

285
00:16:59.890 --> 00:17:04.030
You muddled the mint well. Alejandro.

286
00:17:05.940 --> 00:17:07.770
The lighthouse! Dead ahead!

287
00:17:07.770 --> 00:17:09.630
Aye!

288
00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:17.500
Well. I'm sure Bender's fanny is tired.

289
00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:21.030
As soon as this storm
passes. let's be on our way.

290
00:17:21.030 --> 00:17:25.170
<i>Sargaseous lighthouse. this
is the S.S. Miami Muy Caliente.</i>

291
00:17:25.180 --> 00:17:27.180
Thank you for your glorious beacon.

292
00:17:27.180 --> 00:17:30.610
It saved our lives
and our Saturday night.

293
00:17:30.600 --> 00:17:32.580
<i>Adios.</i>

294
00:17:35.050 --> 00:17:36.560
Your aft-plate.

295
00:17:36.550 --> 00:17:39.920
Its fiery gleam saved a ship
full of South Beach swabbies.

296
00:17:39.930 --> 00:17:43.900
Well. I do polish it every day.
and I sleep in a chamois diaper.

297
00:17:43.900 --> 00:17:47.590
It's a hundred times more reflective
than the mirror in my beacon.

298
00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:49.840
Might I keep it for the lighthouse?

299
00:17:49.830 --> 00:17:51.330
What?! No!

300
00:17:51.340 --> 00:17:54.310
But. Bender. your
buttocks could save lives.

301
00:17:54.310 --> 00:17:55.730
I hate lives!

302
00:17:55.740 --> 00:17:57.880
These are sailors' lives. Bender.

303
00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:01.540
Think of the untold cursing that
would be lost to future generations.

304
00:18:01.550 --> 00:18:04.910
Could you live with that?

305
00:18:05.860 --> 00:18:10.240
You know the answer. you scurvy bastard!

306
00:18:10.250 --> 00:18:14.390
Maybe I have been selfish.
hiding my ass under a bushel.

307
00:18:14.390 --> 00:18:19.760
Perhaps. like all great men. my
ass has a destiny. and if it does.

308
00:18:19.770 --> 00:18:23.250
I can't stand in its way.

309
00:19:00.300 --> 00:19:02.300
Bender. come join us.

310
00:19:02.310 --> 00:19:04.140
<i>We're watching Rear Window.</i>

311
00:19:04.140 --> 00:19:07.140
I used to stick my rear out the window.

312
00:19:07.140 --> 00:19:10.270
<i>If you prefer. we could
watch Behind the Music.</i>

313
00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:12.740
My behind used to make music.

314
00:19:12.750 --> 00:19:14.120
<i>Backdraft is on.</i>

315
00:19:14.120 --> 00:19:16.460
Even my ass wouldn't watch that.

316
00:19:16.460 --> 00:19:19.590
Bender. I'm proud of you
for the sacrifice you made.

317
00:19:19.590 --> 00:19:23.020
Try and find solace in the
fact that somewhere out there.

318
00:19:23.030 --> 00:19:26.510
your keister is doing good.

319
00:19:31.940 --> 00:19:35.640
Well. my shiny friend. yer
days of carousin' are over.

320
00:19:35.640 --> 00:19:40.040
But yer nights of endless.
monotonous rotating have just begun.

321
00:19:40.040 --> 00:19:42.470
Now what say I read you a nice passage

322
00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:47.880
from the scripture to help
you forget yer old master?

323
00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:55.350
In the sanctuary. he made
two cherubim of olive-wood.

324
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.730
Each ten cubits high.

325
00:19:57.730 --> 00:20:00.070
And one wing measured five cubits.

326
00:20:00.060 --> 00:20:05.640
and the other wing measured
five cubits; From the tip...

327
00:20:14.210 --> 00:20:15.310
Oh. no!

328
00:20:15.310 --> 00:20:19.930
Our son Johnny fell
down the gravity well!

329
00:20:23.650 --> 00:20:26.410
Thank you. Assie.

330
00:20:35.690 --> 00:20:38.810
Bender? It's for you.

331
00:20:41.780 --> 00:20:43.610
Assie?

332
00:20:43.620 --> 00:20:46.920
Oh Assie! You came home.

333
00:20:47.080 --> 00:20:49.660
You came home.
